    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process of weaving using one's hands without the use of a loom, joining lengthwise and sideways threads together. One end of the strands are pinned to a stable surface by a bar or nail. Primarily practiced by Native North Americans.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
